      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) is a mechanically robust example of the S54-powered icon. The 3.2L naturally aspirated straight-six features a high-pressure Double VANOS system and individual throttle bodies, providing a sharp, linear throttle response up to the 8,000 RPM redline. Power is delivered through a Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox to a factory variable M-differential. Significant preventative maintenance has been performed, including rear subframe reinforcement and rod bearing replacement, ensuring structural integrity under high lateral loads. The suspension has been refreshed with Bilstein dampers and polyurethane bushings for improved turn-in precision. While the finish shows minor road-rash and typical patina consistent with a well-driven enthusiast vehicle, the engine compression remains within factory specifications and the chassis is free of corrosion.",
